## Step 12.1: Pre-Deployment Checklist

☐ All features tested in development
☐ Database backed up
☐ Video files prepared and named correctly
☐ SMTP credentials configured
☐ Admin password changed from default
☐ SSL certificate installed (for HTTPS)


## Step 12.2: Build for Deployment

In XOJO: Project → Build Settings
Select "Linux" (or your target platform)
Set Application Name: ECHOScore
Click Build
XOJO creates standalone binary


## Step 12.3: Deploy to XOJOWeb Server
Upload built application to server
Set execute permissions:
`bashchmod +x echoscore`

Create systemd service file: /etc/systemd/system/echoscore.service
```
ini[Unit]
Description=ECHOScore Web Application
After=network.target mysql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=www-data
WorkingDirectory=/var/www/echoscore
ExecStart=/var/www/echoscore/echoscore
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

## Phase 12 (continued): Deploy to Server - Part 2
Enable and start service:
bash:
```
sudo systemctl enable echoscore
sudo systemctl start echoscore
sudo systemctl status echoscore
```
You should see "active (running)" status.


## Step 12.4: Configure nginx
Create nginx configuration: /etc/nginx/sites-available/echoscore
```
nginxserver {
    listen 80;
    server_name your-domain.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:8080;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    location /Documents/CaseVideos/ {
        alias /var/www/echoscore/Documents/CaseVideos/;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, max-age=3600";
    }
}
```
## Configure Reverse Proxy - Part 2
Enable site:
bash:
```
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/echoscore /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

## Step 12.5: Install SSL Certificate (Let's Encrypt)
bash
```
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx
sudo certbot --nginx -d your-domain.com
```
Follow prompts to configure HTTPS. Certbot will automatically update your nginx configuration.